<br>
I was wondering how much religion affects a chanter (planning on a inny worshipping de chanter)?  ie will I be kos on the isle in oot even if I manage to get an alliance spell (or whatever it's called) off on a npc b4 going to buy the kiola nuts? and will I be kos in oggok or the inn in freeport?<br>
<br>
how much affect does religion really have regarding faction?<br>
<br>
<br>
Thx <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tahllon>Tahllon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.exaltedcompendium.com/dforum/images/smileys/fee.gif" BORDER=0> at: 5/1/03 11:48:54 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sumlain>Sumlain</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#330000>(5/2/03 7:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfaqs.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=74.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Religion and KoS?</span><hr size=1> The ogres really don't like enchanters (or perhaps don't like inny worshipping enchanters).  My dark elf inny worhshipping enchanter had to wait until ogre illusion to be able to get high enough faction to do the moggok quest.   Oddly, I amiable in ogre form and still had to do alliance to do the quest.  Even more oddly, I don't recall doing any faction work with the ogres but now in ogre form I'm warmly to them without an alliance spell.  I've only done the moggok quest twice (successsfully anyway - screwed it up twice two different ways! :-) ) and didn't think that was enough to raise the faction that high.<br>
<br>
If you use the appropriate illusion and alliance (I think that's a higher level one of what you'll use) you should be fine.   I was very paranoid so I would illusion, cast invis, run to target the turn in mobs and various people around them, run somewhere safe, break invis, and con them.  As long as everyone is dubious, you can then get close enough to cast alliance on them to bring the faction up enough to do the quest.<br>
<br>
Remember...illusion drops when you zone so if you are running around erudin and aren't real familiar with it, keep invis up as there are these transport pads...some cause zoneing and some don't.  I died in the erudin palace when I stepped on the wrong one and the illusion faded! :-)<br>
